items.title: Anthropic taps former Microsoft India MD to lead Bengaluru expansion
items.description: Irina Ghose joins Anthropic as India managing director after 24 years at Microsoft.

items.title: Silicon Valley’s messiest breakup is definitely headed to court
items.description: OpenAI and Microsoft tried to dodge a courtroom showdown with Elon Musk, but a federal judge on Thursday rejected their requests to dismiss the case.

items.description: AI labs just can't get their employees to stay put. Yesterday’s big AI news was the abrupt and seemingly acrimonious departure of three top executives...

items.title: Taiwan to invest $250B in US semiconductor manufacturing
items.description: The U.S. struck a trade deal with Taiwan as the country looks to help boost domestic semiconductor manufacturing.
